	<title>Widgets configuration</title>

		<figure>
			<title>Widgets configuration</title>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center"
						fileref="07-01-DashboardCommonWidgetActions.png" width="95px" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</figure>

		<para>
			Each widget have two kinds of configuration.
		<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
			<para>The first is shared by all widgets, you have to configure which applications are binded to the widget.</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>			
			<para>The second, is specific for each widget, it can be a number of data to show or a time period for example.</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>		
		</para>

		<section id="widgetCommonSetting">
		<title id="widgetCommonSettingXref">Widget common configuration : applications binding</title>
		<para>In the dashboard, click on the "Add a widget", select the type of widget and the corresponding widget and bind the widget with the application that will provide data to the widget.</para>
				
		<para>
			A widget can be bind to one or several application.
			This menu allow you to :
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>Search an application by name, show only application of a project
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Bind an application to the widget, by clicking on the application on the available applications list (Change are automatically saved)
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Unbind an application to the widget, by clicking on the red cross button, in the selected applications list.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Return to dashboard, by clicking on the return button at top right.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</para>
		<figure>
			<title>Example of widget applications configuration</title>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center"
						fileref="07-02-ProjetAndApplicationsConfig.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</figure>
		</section>
</section>
